class Solution {
    public int hammingWeight(int n) {
        int count = 0;
        while (n != 0) {
            count += n & 1;
            n >>= 1;
        }
        return count;
    }
}
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution uses bitwise operations to count the set bits in the binary representation of the input number. The while loop continues until all bits have been processed, and the bitwise AND operation (`n & 1`) checks if the least significant bit is set. The bitwise right shift operation (`n >>= 1`) moves the bits to the right, effectively dividing the number by 2. This approach is efficient because it only requires a constant amount of space and a logarithmic number of operations.

